text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia juncifolia is a shrub or tree belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae that is endemic to north eastern Australia.
text.Description: The shrub or tree typically grows to a height of 3 metres (9.8 ft) and has slender glabrous, reddish-brown branchlets.
text.Distribution: It is native to an area in southern Queensland around Port Lincoln in the north extending into New South Wales to around Glenbrook and extending to about 500 km (310 mi) inland.
